.\" Man page for glassy -- a minimal GPU-accelerated terminal emulator.
.\" Render locally with:  man ./extra/glassy.1
.TH GLASSY 1 "2026-06-24" "glassy" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
glassy \- a minimal, GPU-accelerated terminal emulator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B glassy
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RB [ \-e
.IR COMMAND " [" ARGS ...]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B glassy
is a small, fast, GPU-accelerated terminal emulator written in Rust.
It draws the terminal grid with an instanced
.B wgpu
renderer fed by a dynamic glyph atlas, and stays at 0% idle CPU by
rendering strictly on demand and only re-rasterizing the cells that
actually changed.
.PP
Key capabilities include: 24-bit truecolor and 256-color, color emoji
and CJK fallback, procedural box-drawing, text decorations, mouse
reporting, text selection, clipboard, scrollback, tabs (drag to reorder,
double-click to rename, activity dots), split panes (resize + pane
headers), inline images (kitty graphics protocol and sixel), real-GUI
chrome (settings form, command palette, in-terminal search, help overlay,
menus), 10 live-switchable themes including two light themes,
follow-system light/dark, custom color overrides, theme import, kitty
keyboard protocol levels 1\[en]5, DECCKM, modifyOtherKeys, synchronized
output (DECSET 2026), OSC 7/8/9/52/133 shell integration, URL detection,
session restore, named profiles, config hot-reload, ligatures,
OpenType font features, Powerline glyphs, status bar, configurable
pane headers, per-side padding, fullscreen/maximize, iGPU-default plus
.B GLASSY_GPU
override, and release packages for deb/rpm/AUR/Flatpak/Homebrew/dmg.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-font\-size " PT"
Font size in points. Must be a positive number. Default:
.BR 14 .
.TP
.BI \-\-font\-family " NAME"
Font family name, or a path to a font file.
.TP
.BI \-\-theme " NAME"
Color theme. See
.B THEMES
below. Default:
.BR tokyo-night .
An unknown name falls back to Tokyo Night with a warning.
.TP
.BI \-\-opacity " F"
Window background opacity, 0.0 (fully transparent) to 1.0 (fully opaque).
Clamped to [0,\|1]. Default:
.BR 0.92 .
.TP
.BI \-\-padding " PX"
Grid inset on all sides in logical pixels (\[>=] 0).
.TP
.BI \-\-scrollback " N"
Lines of scrollback history. Default:
.BR 10000 .
.TP
.BI \-\-bell\-visual " BOOL"
Flash the window on the terminal bell. Default
.BR true .
Accepts
.BR true / false ", " yes / no ", " on / off ", " 1 / 0 .
.TP
.BI \-\-bell\-audible " BOOL"
Emit a soft beep on the terminal bell. Default
.BR false .
Requires a build with the
.B bell\-audio
feature.
.TP
.BI \-\-follow\-system " BOOL"
Track the OS light/dark color scheme. When true, the active theme is
chosen from
.B \-\-theme\-light
or
.B \-\-theme\-dark
according to the system preference. Default
.BR false .
.TP
.BI \-\-theme\-light " NAME"
Theme used in system Light mode when
.B \-\-follow\-system
is on. Default
.BR rose\-pine\-dawn .
.TP
.BI \-\-theme\-dark " NAME"
Theme used in system Dark mode when
.B \-\-follow\-system
is on. Default
.BR tokyo\-night .
.TP
.BI \-\-import\-theme " PATH"
Import a color theme from an Alacritty\-compatible TOML file or a base16
YAML file.
.TP
.BI \-\-status\-bar " BOOL"
Show the status bar at the bottom. Default
.BR false .
.TP
.BI \-\-pane\-headers " BOOL"
Show per-pane title bars (with the close box and split menu) when the
tab is split. Default
.BR true .
.TP
.BI \-\-ligatures " BOOL"
Enable OpenType
.B liga
ligature shaping across cell runs. Default
.BR false .
.TP
.BI \-\-font\-features " LIST"
Comma- or space-separated list of OpenType feature tags to force on or
off, e.g.
.BR "ss01,calt=0" .
Each entry is a bare 4-char tag (enable) or
.BI tag = N
(explicit value; 0 = disable).
.TP
.BI \-\-word\-separator " STR"
Extra characters treated as word boundaries during double-click
selection.
.TP
.BI \-\-cwd " PATH"
Working directory for the first tab's shell.
.TP
.BI \-\-restore\-session " [BOOL]"
Restore the previous session's tabs, splits, and working directories.
Bare
.B \-\-restore\-session
is equivalent to
.BR \-\-restore\-session\~true .
Default
.BR false .
.TP
.BI \-\-profile " NAME"
Activate a
.B [profile.NAME]
section from the config file. Profile keys are overlaid before CLI
flags, so CLI flags still win.
.TP
.BI \-e ", " \-\-command " COMMAND " [ ARGS ...]
Run
.I COMMAND
(with the remaining arguments) instead of the login shell. This consumes
the rest of the command line, so it must come last.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B glassy
reads
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/glassy/glassy.conf
(falling back to
.IR ~/.config/glassy/glassy.conf ).
On macOS:
.IR "~/Library/Application Support/glassy/glassy.conf" .
The file is a list of
.I KEY=VALUE
lines. Blank lines and lines beginning with
.B #
or
.B ;
are ignored. Surrounding whitespace and one layer of matching quotes are
stripped from values. Command-line options override the file.
.PP
Recognized keys (defaults in brackets):
.TP
.B font_family
Font family name or path to a font file. [FiraCode Nerd Font Mono]
.TP
.B font_size
Font size in points. [14]
.TP
.B theme
Active color theme. See
.B THEMES
below. [tokyo-night]
.TP
.B opacity
Window background opacity 0.0\[en]1.0. [0.92]
.TP
.B padding
Uniform grid inset in logical px (\[>=] 0). [6]
.TP
.BR padding_top ", " padding_bottom ", " padding_left ", " padding_right
Per-side padding overrides. When set, override the uniform
.B padding
for that side.
.TP
.B shell
Program plus arguments, e.g.
.IR "/usr/bin/zsh -l" .
[login shell]
.TP
.B scrollback
Lines of scrollback history (0\[en]1000000). [10000]
.TP
.B bell_visual
Flash the window on the terminal bell. [true]
.TP
.B bell_audible
Soft beep on the bell (needs
.B bell\-audio
build). [false]
.TP
.B follow_system
Track the OS light/dark color scheme. [false]
.TP
.B theme_light
Theme used when the system is in Light mode. [rose-pine-dawn]
.TP
.B theme_dark
Theme used when the system is in Dark mode. [tokyo-night]
.TP
.B status_bar
Show the status bar at the bottom. [false]
.TP
.B pane_headers
Show per-pane title bars in splits. [true]
.TP
.B ligatures
Enable OpenType
.B liga
shaping across cell runs. [false]
.TP
.B font_features
Comma- or space-separated OpenType feature tags to force on/off,
e.g.\&
.BR "ss01, calt=0" .
[empty]
.TP
.B word_separator
Extra characters treated as word boundaries for double-click selection.
[empty]
.TP
.B cwd
Initial working directory for the first tab's shell.
.TP
.B restore_session
Restore the previous session's tabs/splits/cwds on launch. [false]
.PP
Custom color overrides (6-digit hex, with or without leading
.BR # ):
.TP
.BR color.fg ", " color.bg ", " color.cursor ", " color.selection_bg
Override the theme's corresponding special color.
.TP
.BI color.ansi N
Override ANSI palette entry
.I N
(0\[en]15).
.SS PROFILES
Named profiles live in
.B [profile.NAME]
sections. Any top-level key (including
.B color.*
overrides) is valid inside a profile. Activate a profile with
.BR \-\-profile\~NAME .
Example:
.PP
.RS
.EX
[profile.work]
theme    = catppuccin\-mocha
font_size = 16
cwd      = /home/me/work
color.fg = #cdd6f4
.EE
.RE
.SH THEMES
Ten built-in themes selectable by name:
.PP
.RS
.TS
l l.
\fBtokyo-night\fR	dark (default)
\fBcatppuccin-mocha\fR	dark
\fBcatppuccin-macchiato\fR	dark
\fBgruvbox-dark\fR	dark
\fBdracula\fR	dark
\fBnord\fR	dark
\fBsolarized-dark\fR	dark
\fBrose-pine\fR	dark
\fBrose-pine-dawn\fR	light
\fBcatppuccin-latte\fR	light
.TE
.RE
.PP
Names are case-insensitive and separator-insensitive (e.g.
.BR "tokyo night" " = " tokyonight " = " tokyo-night ).
Themes can be switched live in the settings overlay
.RB ( Ctrl+, )
or via the command palette
.RB ( Ctrl+Shift+P ).
An external Alacritty TOML or base16 YAML theme can be imported with
.BR \-\-import\-theme .
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.SS Tabs
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+T
Open a new tab.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+W
Close the focused pane; falls back to closing the tab when only one pane remains.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Tab
Switch to the next tab.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+Tab
Switch to the previous tab.
.TP
.B Double-click tab chip
Open the inline rename editor (Enter commits, Esc cancels).
.TP
.B Drag tab chip
Reorder tabs by dragging a chip left or right.
.SS Split panes
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+E
Split the focused pane vertically (left | right).
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+O
Split the focused pane horizontally (top / bottom).
.TP
.B Alt+Arrow
Move focus to the adjacent pane in the arrow direction (Left / Right / Up / Down).
.TP
.B Drag gutter
Resize the pane by dragging the divider.
.SS Clipboard
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+C
Copy the current selection to the clipboard.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+V
Paste from the clipboard.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Left-click
Open the OSC 8 hyperlink (or plain-text URL) under the pointer.
.TP
.B Right-click
Context menu (copy / paste / open link).
.SS Overlays and tools
.TP
.B Ctrl+,
Settings overlay: font size, opacity, bell, theme, font family, scrollback,
status bar, pane headers. Tab/arrows navigate fields, Enter saves to the
config file, Esc closes.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+P
Command palette: fuzzy-searchable list of every action and setting.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+F
In-terminal search: regex find bar with match highlighting;
Enter = next match, Shift+Enter = previous match, Esc closes.
.TP
.B F1
Help overlay: scrollable keybinding cheat-sheet.
.TP
.B Esc
Close the active overlay (settings, help, palette, search).
.SS View and font
.TP
.BR "Ctrl++" ", " "Ctrl+="
Increase the font size.
.TP
.B Ctrl+-
Decrease the font size.
.TP
.B Ctrl+0
Reset the font size to its configured value.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+B
Toggle the status bar.
.TP
.BR Shift+PageUp ", " Shift+PageDown
Scroll up / down through the scrollback.
.TP
.BR Shift+Home ", " Shift+End
Scroll to the top / bottom of the scrollback.
.SS Window
.TP
.B F11
Toggle borderless fullscreen.
.TP
.B F10
Toggle maximize.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GLASSY_GPU=high
.TQ
.B GLASSY_GPU=discrete
Use the high-performance (discrete) GPU instead of the default
integrated / low-power adapter.
.TP
.B GLASSY_GPU=low
.TQ
.B GLASSY_GPU=integrated
Explicit low-power GPU selection (same as the default).
.TP
.B WGPU_ADAPTER_NAME=<name>
Pin a specific wgpu adapter by name.
.TP
.B GLASSY_CAPTURE=<path.ppm>
Headless mode: render after a short delay, write a PPM screenshot,
then exit. Useful for CI and testing.
.TP
.B GLASSY_CAPTURE_MS=<ms>
Override the headless capture delay (default ~100 ms).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/glassy/glassy.conf
Primary configuration file (Linux).
.TP
.I ~/.config/glassy/glassy.conf
Fallback configuration file (Linux, when
.B $XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is unset).
.TP
.I ~/Library/Application Support/glassy/glassy.conf
Configuration file on macOS.
.TP
.I $XDG_STATE_HOME/glassy/session.json
.TQ
.I ~/.local/state/glassy/session.json
Session persistence file (tabs, splits, cwds). Written on exit;
loaded on launch when
.B restore_session = true
is set.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/glassy/fonts/NotoColorEmoji.ttf
Bundled color-emoji font loaded at runtime, if present.
